Over the course of two years, I have driven by this place so many times, but I never had the time to check it out because parking isn't readily availabile.  This night happened to be the right time to give it a try, because I was already in the neighborhood, visiting a friend. When I came in the early evening, there were about 7 other people enjoying the Japanese food, probably because the dinner rush had not started yet.  Tonight I was in the mood for the chicken and beef hibachi.  It seemed healthy enough because it ncludedhich included mostly broccoli, and noodles of course.  After I placed my order,  they had the food prepared in a short amount of of time.  This dinner wiith a fountain drink came out to be around $10.00, which didn't seem expensive at all! The inside of the restaurant was clean, despite a couple of loud raunchy folks, it was a nice environment. The employeee who helped me was fast and friendly! I haven't seen too many of these restaurants around Washington, but hopefully some day they will be more commonplace.

That to me seems like a punishing tactic for customers. If they want to pie the sauce on themselves to their liking that experience is ruined due to the poor customer service offered. You charging them looks like your business is failing or scrambling for change. It costs about .03-.05 cents for those little plastic containers, I know because I make the same purchases at my reataurant. It’s sad because the food is great but their customer service and business practices as insane. You should really rethink your approach to how you treat your customers.
